<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>GitHub Trending Magazine Export, {{ issue_label|title }} Issue</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=Playfair+Display:wght@600;700;800&family=Source+Serif+4:opsz,wght@8..60,400;8..60,600;8..60,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
      @page {
        size: 1600px 900px;
        margin: 0;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html,
      body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: "Source Serif 4", Georgia, serif;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }

      .page {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        overflow: hidden;
        page-break-after: always;
        break-after: page;
      }

      .page:last-child {
        page-break-after: auto;
        break-after: auto;
      }

      .page.light {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2f2ee 0%, #e9e9e4 100%);
        color: #101010;
      }

      .page.dark {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #080808 0%, #111111 100%);
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.94);
      }

      .page-inner {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        padding: 4vh 4vw 8vh;
      }

      .cover,
      .back-cover {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: space-between;
        min-height: 100%;
      }

      .cover-top,
      .cover-bottom,
      .back-cover-top,
      .back-cover-bottom {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 2vw;
      }

      .kicker,
      .cover-meta,
      .mini-meta,
      .repo-meta,
      .back-note {
        font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
        font-size: max(12px, 0.95vw);
        line-height: 1.5;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .page.light .kicker,
      .page.light .cover-meta,
      .page.light .mini-meta,
      .page.light .repo-meta,
      .page.light .back-note {
        color: rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.76);
      }

      .page.dark .kicker,
      .page.dark .cover-meta,
      .page.dark .mini-meta,
      .page.dark .repo-meta,
      .page.dark .back-note {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
      }

      .cover-title,
      .back-title {
        margin: 0;
        max-width: 72vw;
        font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
        font-size: 9.3vw;
        line-height: 0.92;
        letter-spacing: -0.05em;
      }

      .cover-deck,
      .back-deck {
        max-width: 48vw;
        margin: 2vh 0 0;
        font-size: max(17px, 1.38vw);
        line-height: 1.45;
      }

      .cover-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 55fr 45fr;
        align-items: end;
        gap: 3vw;
        width: 100%;
        flex: 1;
        min-height: 0;
      }

      .cover-aside {
        align-self: end;
        padding-bottom: 0;
      }

      .spread {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 55fr 45fr;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        gap: 2.6vw;
      }

      .spread-left,
      .spread-right {
        position: relative;
        min-width: 0;
      }

      .spread-left {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: flex-start;
        padding-right: 1vw;
      }

      .spread-right {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding-left: 2.2vw;
      }

      .page.light .spread-right {
        border-left: 1px solid rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.12);
      }

      .page.dark .spread-right {
        border-left: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
      }

      .rank-ghost {
        position: absolute;
        top: -1.5vh;
        left: -0.2vw;
        z-index: 0;
        font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
        font-size: 21vw;
        line-height: 0.8;
        letter-spacing: -0.08em;
      }

      .page.light .rank-ghost {
        color: rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.08);
      }

      .page.dark .rank-ghost {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
      }

      .left-content,
      .right-content {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      .left-content {
        padding-top: 7vh;
      }

      .category-tag {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 2.2vh;
        padding-bottom: 0.5vh;
        border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
      }

      .headline {
        margin: 0 0 2.6vh;
        font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
        font-size: 4.85vw;
        line-height: 0.96;
        letter-spacing: -0.045em;
      }

      .repo-path {
        margin: 0 0 2vh;
        font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
        font-size: max(17px, 1.12vw);
        line-height: 1.45;
        word-break: break-word;
      }

      .description {
        max-width: 40vw;
        margin: 0 0 2.4vh;
        font-size: max(17px, 1.22vw);
        line-height: 1.42;
      }

      .page.light .description {
        color: rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.9);
      }

      .page.dark .description {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);
      }

      .star-count {
        margin: 0 0 1.4vh;
        font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
        font-size: 6.1vw;
        line-height: 0.88;
        letter-spacing: -0.05em;
      }

      .stat-line {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 1vw 1.4vw;
        margin-bottom: 2.2vh;
      }

      .stat-pill {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        min-height: 2.7em;
        padding: 0.25em 0;
      }

      .callout {
        margin-top: 1vh;
        padding: 1.5vh 1.1vw 1.7vh 1.3vw;
        border-left: 4px solid currentColor;
      }

      .page.light .callout {
        background: rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.06);
      }

      .page.dark .callout {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.09);
      }

      .callout-label {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 1.2vh;
      }

      .callout p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: max(16px, 1.14vw);
        line-height: 1.42;
      }

      .page.light .callout p {
        color: rgba(16, 16, 16, 0.82);
      }

      .page.dark .callout p {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="page dark">
      <div class="page-inner cover">
        <div class="cover-top">
          <div class="kicker">GitHub Trends / {{ issue_label }} Issue / {{ issue_date }}</div>
          <div class="cover-meta">Monochrome export / print-ready magazine</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-grid">
          <div>
            <h1 class="cover-title">GitHub Trending Magazine</h1>
            <p class="cover-deck">A full-bleed export edition built from the same weekly issue data: 12 trending repos, editorial framing, and practical notes on how each one could matter to your work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cover-aside">
            <div class="mini-meta">Page 01 / Cover</div>
            <p class="cover-deck">This print/export variant keeps the same monochrome magazine system but stacks pages vertically so it can render cleanly to PDF.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-bottom">
          <div class="cover-meta">Fonts / Playfair Display, Source Serif 4, IBM Plex Mono</div>
          <div class="cover-meta">Generated / {{ generated_at }}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {% for repo in repos %}
    {% set page_number = loop.index + 1 %}
    {% set theme = 'dark' if page_number % 2 == 1 else 'light' %}
    <section class="page {{ theme }}">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="spread">
          <div class="spread-left">
            <div class="rank-ghost">{{ '%02d'|format(repo.rank) }}</div>
            <div class="left-content">
              <div class="kicker category-tag">{{ repo.category }}</div>
              <h2 class="headline">{{ repo.headline }}</h2>
              <p class="repo-path">{{ repo.owner }}/{{ repo.repo }}</p>
              <p class="description">{{ repo.description }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="spread-right">
            <div class="right-content">
              <div class="mini-meta">Page {{ '%02d'|format(page_number) }} / Rank {{ '%02d'|format(repo.rank) }}</div>
              <div class="star-count">{{ repo.stars }}</div>
              <div class="stat-line repo-meta">
                <span class="stat-pill">{{ repo.language }}</span>
                <span class="stat-pill">{{ repo.trend }}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="callout">
                <span class="callout-label mini-meta">How to use this</span>
                <p>{{ repo.note }}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="repo-meta">{{ repo.url }}</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    {% endfor %}

    <section class="page dark">
      <div class="page-inner back-cover">
        <div class="back-cover-top">
          <div class="kicker">Back cover / {{ issue_label }} Issue / {{ issue_date }}</div>
          <div class="cover-meta">12 repos / {{ total_pages }} pages / monochrome only</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="back-title">What matters is the pattern, not the hype.</h2>
          <p class="back-deck">If a repo stays with you after the page turn, translate it into one sentence: what system behavior, workflow pattern, or design instinct does it sharpen for your own work?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="back-cover-bottom">
          <div class="back-note">This edition is designed for PDF export and paged reading.</div>
          <div class="back-note">{% if issue_note %}{{ issue_note }}{% else %}Window / {{ issue_label }}{% endif %}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
